# Comic Drama Workflow Cursor Rules

Cursor is primarily responsible for focused frontend and local interaction
work in this repository.

## Preferred Cursor Tasks

- UI layout and interaction fixes
- `frontend/app.js` component-level edits
- `frontend/styles.css` visual polish
- review console ergonomics
- metadata display
- small documentation edits

## Avoid Unless Explicitly Assigned

- `scripts/run_workflow.py`
- `backend/project_runtime.py`
- `video_providers.py`
- `scripts/video_provider_adapters.py`
- `backend/video_generation.py`
- provider routing architecture
- canonical timeline schema changes

If a task requires those files, ask for a Codex/Kiro handoff or an accepted
spec first.

## Frontend Check

After editing `frontend/app.js`, run:

```powershell
node --check frontend\app.js
```

If local `node` is unavailable, ask the maintainer or Codex to run the bundled
Node check.

## UI Contract

Do not invent backend fields casually. Prefer existing project fields:

- `canonical_timeline`
- `scene.assets`
- `scene.review_meta`
- `scene.provider_meta`
- `scene.consistency_meta`
- `scene.director_meta`
- `scene.temporal_spec`

For new fields, update or request a spec before implementing.

## Coordination

Do not make large unrelated refactors while polishing UI. Keep edits scoped and
leave backend integration to Codex unless explicitly assigned.
